## Recipe 4: FAQ

**Primary Role**: Operator, Customer
**When to generate**: If Operator or Customer role is involved

### Recommended Structure

1. General Questions (what is this process?)
2. Operator Questions (how do I do X?)
3. Customer Questions (what happens to me?)
4. Edge Cases (what if Y happens?)
5. Quick Contact (who to reach for more questions)

### Writing Tips

- Maximum 3 sentences per answer. Link to SOP/process-brief for details.
- Group by role, not by topic.
- Update FAQ when new edge cases are discovered (link to L6 cases-library).
- Include "Last Updated" date at top.

### Tone Sample (Operator FAQ)

> **Q: How do I know if this refund is eligible for full refund?**
> A: Check purchase date (≤ 7 days) AND course progress (< 25%). Both must be true. See SOP Step S1 for detailed instructions.

> **Q: What if the customer paid via WeChat and Stripe doesn't have the transaction?**
> A: Check the WeChat Pay merchant portal instead. Transaction prefix is `wx_`. Escalate to Finance if neither system has the record.

### Tone Sample (Customer FAQ)

> **Q: How long will my refund take?**
> A: Within 5-7 business days after approval. You'll receive an SMS when the refund is initiated, and another when it reaches your account.

### Anti-Example (DO NOT DO THIS)

> Q: 能退款吗？
> A: 看情况。

**Why it's bad**: No decision criteria, no link to detailed procedure, unhelpfully vague.

