## Recipe 10: Stakeholder One-Pager

**Primary Role**: Executive Sponsor, Customer
**When to generate**: If Executive or Customer role is involved

### Recommended Structure
1. Process Name & One-Liner
2. Scope (what it covers, what it doesn't)
3. Key SLA Commitments (top 3 numbers)
4. Roles at a Glance (who does what, max 5 roles)
5. Process Flow (simplified 5-7 step diagram)
6. Key Risks & Mitigations (top 3)
7. Contact (who to reach for questions)

### Writing Tips
- One page. Strict limit. If it doesn't fit, cut less important sections.
- Numbers first: executives and customers care about time and cost.
- Use simple language: "You'll get your refund within 7 days" not "SLA resolution time ≤ 7 business days"
- Risk section: what could go wrong AND what we do about it

### Tone Sample
> **Customer Refund Process — At a Glance**
> 
> **What happens when you request a refund**: We'll first try to understand your concern and see if we can help. If you still want to proceed, your refund will be processed within 3-7 business days.
>
> **Key Numbers**: First response ≤ 24h | Refund to account ≤ 7 business days | 95% of refunds processed without escalation

### Anti-Example
> 本流程覆盖退款全链路，涉及8个角色14个步骤，详见 process-brief.md L1.4。
> **Why it's bad**: Too internal, too detailed, no customer-facing language, just a pointer.

